%N A246639 Sequence a(n) = 3 + 5*A001519(n+1) appearing in a certain three circle touching problem, together with A246638.
%C A246639 See the comments under A246638. The curvature c(n) defined there is c(n) = A246638(n) + (4*a(n)/5)*phi with phi = (1+sqrt(5))/2, the golden section. It lives in the quadratic number field Q(sqrt(5)). Descartes' theorem on touching circles gives c(n) = -4/5 + A(n) + A(n+1) + 2*sqrt((-4/5 )*(A(n) + A(n+1)) + A(n)*A(n+1)), with A(n) = A092387(n), n >= 0. For the proof of the first formula given below one compares this a(n) with the a(n) in c(n) given above. This uses standard Chebyshev S-polynomial identities with x = 3, like the three term recurrence and the Cassini-Simson type identity S(n, x)*S(n-2, x) = -1 + S(n-1, x)^2 (here for x=3). This implies S(n, 3)*S(n-1, 3) = (-1 + S(n, 3)^2 + S(n-1, 3)^2)/3. See also the W. Lang link in A092387, part III a).
